My Experience Building This Project

Before starting this project, I was curious about what “vibe coding” actually meant and which tools supported it. Initially, I assumed it was simply using ctrl+c and ctrl+d in the code generated by AI and 
making small edits. I tried approaching this project the same way.

But very soon, I realized that this approach was not working. The AI generated code that I did not fully understand. There were modules and concepts that were new to me. I felt confused and stuck because I was 
using code without knowing how it actually worked. I understood that if I continued like this, I would not learn anything meaningful.

So I changed my approach. Instead of just using the code, I started studying the architecture and logic behind it. I compared what the AI generated with what I thought made sense. While doing this, I found 
several errors in the AI-generated code and fixed them myself. Debugging those mistakes helped me learn much more than simply copying code.

This project helped me understand that vibe coding is not about blindly using AI. It is about working with AI while using your own thinking and logic. Along with learning about Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA), 
I also learned how important it is to truly understand the code you write.
